\label{prop:boundedtightness}
  Let $\mathbf{u}\in\mathcal{Z}_{1/2}^{N}$
  solve \cref{eq:uPDE-1} with bounded initial condition $\mathbf{u}(0,\cdot)\in L^{\infty}(\mathbb{R})^{N}$.
  Then the family of random variables $\{\mathbf{u}(t,\cdot)\}_{t\ge1}$
  is tight with respect to the topology of $\mathcal{X}_{1/2}^{N}$,
  and
  \begin{equation}
    \sup_{t\ge0,x\in\mathbb{R}}\mathbb{E}|\mathbf{u}(t,x)|^{2}<\infty.\label{eq:supu2bdd}
  \end{equation}

